        <link href="AddingXMLidsSmallDoc.dita#task_lgt_m5p_ht" class="- topic/link " xtrf="/Users/ilovan/Documentation/DToC/AddingXMLIndex.dita" xtrc="link:2;78:65" type="task"><?ditaot gentext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext ">Adding XML ids to your document manually</linktext><?ditaot genshortdesc?><desc class="- topic/desc ">DToC uses XML ids as index locators; every index item is associated with one or more         paragraph (as opposed to pages in print indexes). </desc></link>
        <link href="AddingXMLidsOxygen.dita#task_vqx_qyp_ht" class="- topic/link " xtrf="/Users/ilovan/Documentation/DToC/AddingXMLIndex.dita" xtrc="link:3;79:63" type="task"><?ditaot gentext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext ">Adding XML ids with oXygen</linktext><?ditaot genshortdesc?><desc class="- topic/desc ">This option is best for large DToC documents. The downside of using oXygen to insert         IDs is that they are not human readable. It may be worth using the tool, if you are able to         use a script to transform the ID pattern. </desc></link>
